\nof the cockpit recording',-1),(128631,5,168828,168904,'01:57:14.528','01:57:17.697','to highlight a key moment\non board flight 227,',-1),(128632,5,168910,168970,'01:57:17.948','01:57:20.450','wherein you say, \"We\'re going to roll it.\"',-1),(128633,5,168978,169030,'01:57:20.785','01:57:22.952','\"Here we go. I\'ve got control.\"',-1),(128634,5,169036,169121,'01:57:23.204','01:57:26.748','You made a very conscious decision\nto invert the aircraft,',-1),(128635,5,169123,169191,'01:57:26.832','01:57:29.626','to roll the plane upside down,\nis that correct?',-1),(128636,5,169267,169335,'01:57:32.797','01:57:35.632','I\'m not sure if it was conscious. But...',-1),(128637,5,169371,169419,'01:57:37.134','01:57:39.135','it was more like instinct.',-1),(128638,5,169447,169495,'01:57:40.304','01:57:42.305','What led to that decision?',-1),(128639,5,169595,169627,'01:57:46.477','01:57:47.811','I don\'t recall.',-1),(128640,5,169635,169686,'01:57:48.145','01:57:50.271','Let me quote from\nan investigative summary.',-1),(128641,5,169688,169743,'01:57:50.356','01:57:52.649','\"From 9:34 until 9:42,',-1),(128642,5,169745,169817,'01:57:52.733','01:57:55.735','\"the events on the aircraft are,\"\nagain I quote,',-1),(128643,5,169819,169871,'01:57:55.820','01:57:57.987','\"bold and remarkable.',-1),(128644,5,169879,169963,'01:57:58.322','01:58:01.825','\"By inverting the plane,\nCaptain Whitaker arrested the descent',-1),(128645,5,169969,170029,'01:58:02.076','01:58:04.577','\"and allowed the aircraft to level off,',-1),(128646,5,170035,170127,'01:58:04.829','01:58:08.665','\"enabling him to glide the aircraft\naway from any populated areas\"',-1),(128647,5,170133,170234,'01:58:08.916','01:58:13.086','\"and allowing him to execute\na forced landing in an open field.\"',-1),(128648,5,170460,170524,'01:58:22.513','01:58:25.181','I heard a loud metallic bang.',-1),(128649,5,170540,170592,'01:58:25.850','01:58:28.017','We pitched nose down.',-1),(128650,5,170632,170664,'01:58:29.687','01:58:31.020','- No control.\n- Yes.',-1),(128651,5,170672,170742,'01:58:31.355','01:58:34.274','First Officer Evans\'\ntestimony confirms the same.',-1),(128652,5,170808,170852,'01:58:37.027','01:58:38.862','I want to show you something.',-1),(128653,5,170956,171004,'01:58:43.200','01:58:45.201','Nothing\'s happening.',-1),(128654,5,171020,171049,'01:58:45.870','01:58:47.078','This remote isn\'t working.',-1),(128655,5,171051,171112,'01:58:47.163','01:58:49.706','Apologies. I can do this manually.',-1),(128656,5,171381,171445,'01:59:00.885','01:59:03.553','This is the jackscrew\non the tail assembly',-1),(128657,5,171447,171521,'01:59:03.637','01:59:06.723','that articulates the horizontal stabilizer,',-1),(128658,5,171525,171561,'01:59:06.891','01:59:08.391','also known as the elevator.',-1),(128659,5,171563,171592,'01:59:08.476','01:59:09.684','As you can see,',-1),(128660,5,171599,171674,'01:59:09.977','01:59:13.104','the threads on this screw\nare almost entirely gone.',-1),(128661,5,171685,171763,'01:59:13.564','01:59:16.816','This part was suggested as\na maintenance replacement',-1),(128662,5,171771,171860,'01:59:17.151','01:59:20.862','in January of 2011.\nIt was never replaced.',-1),(128663,5,171873,171943,'01:59:21.405','01:59:24.324','It had an additional\n1,200 hours of flight on it.',-1),(128664,5,171945,171973,'01:59:24.408','01:59:25.575','It finally failed.',-1),(128665,5,171976,172036,'01:59:25.701','01:59:28.203','Our investigators have concluded',-1),(128666,5,172047,172091,'01:59:28.662','01:59:30.497','that the jackscrew snapped',-1),(128667,5,172097,172186,'01:59:30.748','01:59:34.417','and the elevator was frozen\nin a fixed position,',-1),(128668,5,172194,172255,'01:59:34.752','01:59:37.295','locking the elevator in a down position,',-1),(128669,5,172257,172314,'01:59:37.379','01:59:39.756','which forced the plane into a dive.',-1),(128670,5,172322,172412,'01:59:40.090','01:59:43.843','The loss of the elevator was,\nand I quote our report,',-1),(128671,5,172414,172498,'01:59:43.928','01:59:47.430','\"A catastrophic event\nfrom which recovery was improbable\"',-1),(128672,5,172500,172553,'01:59:47.515','01:59:49.724','\"and stable flight impossible.\"',-1),(128673,5,172646,172678,'01:59:53.604','01:59:54.938','Mr. Whitaker,',-1),(128674,5,172698,172745,'01:59:55.773','01:59:57.732','I want to talk about the days leading',-1),(128675,5,172747,172810,'01:59:57.817','02:00:00.443','and the hours leading\nup to the accident.',-1),(128676,5,172813,172839,'02:00:00.569','02:00:01.653','But before I do,',-1),(128677,5,172841,172883,'02:00:01.737','02:00:03.488','I want to remind you\nthat you are under oath',-1),(128678,5,172885,172928,'02:00:03.572','02:00:05.365','and that any testimony\nyou give here today',-1),(128679,5,172930,172964,'02:00:05.449','02:00:06.866','will be considered admissible',-1),(128680,5,172967,173033,'02:00:06.992','02:00:09.744','in any subsequent hearings\nor criminal proceedings.',-1),(128681,5,173038,173086,'02:00:09.954','02:00:11.955','Do you understand what that means?',-1),(128682,5,173135,173220,'02:00:13.999','02:00:17.502','Captain Whitaker, for the record,\nI need you to verbalize your answer.',-1),(128683,5,173250,173306,'02:00:18.754','02:00:21.089','I\'m sorry. Yes, I understand.',-1),(128684,5,173317,173369,'02:00:21.549','02:00:23.716','On the three days\nleading up to the accident,',-1),(128685,5,173371,173409,'02:00:23.801','02:00:25.385','Tuesday, October 11th,',-1),(128686,5,173411,173495,'02:00:25.469','02:00:28.972','Wednesday, October 12th\nor Thursday, October 13th,',-1),(128687,5,173497,173595,'02:00:29.056','02:00:33.142','did you consume any alcohol\nor other intoxicating elements?',-1),(128688,5,173618,173650,'02:00:34.103','02:00:35.436','No, I did not.',-1),(128689,5,173661,173702,'02:00:35.896','02:00:37.605','On the morning of the accident,',-1),(128690,5,173708,173757,'02:00:37.857','02:00:39.899','Friday, October 14th,',-1),(128691,5,173759,173883,'02:00:39.984','02:00:45.154','did you consume any alcohol\nor ingest any chemicals or drugs',-1),(128692,5,173885,173973,'02:00:45.239','02:00:48.908','that may have impaired\nyour ability to perform your job?',-1),(128693,5,173983,174023,'02:00:49.326','02:00:50.994','No, I did not.',-1),(128694,5,174044,174131,'02:00:51.871','02:00:55.498','Mr. Whitaker, do you now\nor have you ever had',-1),(128695,5,174133,174187,'02:00:55.583','02:00:57.792','a problem with alcohol dependency,',-1),(128696,5,174189,174248,'02:00:57.877','02:01:00.336','alcoholism or drug addiction?',-1),(128697,5,174256,174280,'02:01:00.671','02:01:01.671','No.',-1),(128698,5,174336,174388,'02:01:04.008','02:01:06.175','Okay, Mr. Whitaker, we\'re about done.',-1),(128699,5,174558,174648,'02:01:13.267','02:01:17.020','Due to the severe turbulence\nin the early part of the flight,',-1),(128700,5,174650,174706,'02:01:17.104','02:01:19.439','you asked the flight crew to suspend',-1),(128701,5,174708,174756,'02:01:19.523','02:01:21.524','the beverage service\non the plane, is that correct?',-1),(128702,5,174761,174785,'02:01:21.734','02:01:22.734','Yes, that\'s correct.',-1),(128703,5,174790,174850,'02:01:22.943','02:01:25.445','I suspended\nthe drink service on the plane.',-1),(128704,5,174852,174911,'02:01:25.529','02:01:27.989','Are you aware that\nour investigators found',-1),(128705,5,174913,174999,'02:01:28.073','02:01:31.659','two single service vodka bottles\nin the galley trash bin?',-1),(128706,5,175056,175088,'02:01:34.038','02:01:35.371','Yes, I\'m aware of that.',-1),(128707,5,175120,175177,'02:01:36.707','02:01:39.042','There were five crew members on board',-1),(128708,5,175179,175241,'02:01:39.126','02:01:41.711','that would have had access\nto the beverage trolley.',-1),(128709,5,175249,175295,'02:01:42.046','02:01:43.963','Less than an hour after the accident,',-1),(128710,5,175297,175344,'02:01:44.048','02:01:46.007','blood was taken from each\nof these crew members,',-1),(12871